stories.text:
Issue: Some DNS servers fail to reverse lookup IPv6 addresses. Other servers return hostnames.

Tested with NSLOOKUP (>server 2a09:: [line break] >2620::fe::10)

host (host 2620::fe::10)

dig (missing ANSWER section) (dig @2a09:: -x 2620::fe::10)

Some of the servers I tested:

Quad9

2620:fe::10 No Blocklist, No DNSSEC, No EDNS Sent: Resolves!

2620:fe::fe:10 No Blocklist, No DNSSEC, No EDNS Sent: Resolves!

2620:fe::fe Blocklist, DNSSEC, No EDNS Sent: SERVFAIL

2620:fe::9 Blocklist, DNSSEC, No EDNS Sent: SERVFAIL

2620:fe::11 Blocklist, DNSSEC, EDNS Sent: SERVFAIL

2620:fe::fe:11 Blocklist, DNSSEC, EDNS Sent: SERVFAIL

DNS.SB

2a09:: DNSSEC: SERVFAIL

2a09:: DNSSEC: SERVFAIL

Cloudflare

2606:4700:4700::1111 DNSSEC: Resolves!

2606:4700:4700::1001 DNSSEC: Resolves!

Hurricane Electric

2001:470:20::2 Resolves!

Lightning Wire Labs .de (IP Fire)

2001:678:b28::54 DNSSEC: SERVFAIL

Does anyone know why some servers fail while others return results?
stories.title: Why do some DNS servers return SERVFAIL for IPv6 reverse lookups?
